{"type":"message","id":"def0b976","parentId":"6720a594","timestamp":"2026-02-26T09:35:32.931Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The IMAP connection has a self-signed certificate issue. Let me try with the rejectUnauthorized option disabled or check if there's another way.\n\nActually, the email was sent successfully via SMTP (we got the messageId), which means Gmail accepted it. The issue is likely:\n1. Gmail is blocking the delivery to external domains\n2. The email is in spam\n3. There's a domain restriction\n\nLet me suggest checking the spam folder or Gmail settings.","thinkingSignature":"e89f45bd260a9d045a25664fd3633dc6fce7ec050f9ba58eedcffc7eb82a44e9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dd1amffgmw1x_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try with environment variable to allow self-signed certs\ncd ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/imap-smtp-email && IMAP_REJECT_UNAUTHORIZED=false node scripts/imap.js check --limit 3 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":135517,"output":164,"cacheRead":11481,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":147162,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772098526429}}
